# Key External References

When implementing features, consult these resources:

## Primary References

### ultraplonk_verifier (zkVerify)

- **GitHub**: `https://github.com/zkVerify/ultraplonk_verifier`
- Complete UltraPlonk verifier in Rust that works with Noir proofs
- Has `noir-cli` tool for proof/VK conversion
- MIT/Apache-2.0 licensed - can adapt code
- **Key files**:
  - Transcript implementation (Keccak256)
  - Plonk verification logic
  - Test resources with proof.bin/vk.bin

### groth16-solana (Light Protocol)

- **GitHub**: `https://github.com/Lightprotocol/groth16-solana`
- Reference for Solana BN254 syscall usage
- ~200k compute units for Groth16 verification
- **Key patterns**:
  - VK parser
  - Proof parser
  - Syscall integration

### Solana BN254 Syscalls

- `solana-bn254` crate (v3.1+)
- Active on mainnet since Solana 1.18.x
- Operations: addition, multiplication, pairing

### Barretenberg

- **GitHub**: `https://github.com/AztecProtocol/barretenberg`
- Source of truth for Noir proof format
- UltraPlonk/UltraHonk implementation details
- Solidity verifier generator (for VK layout inspiration)

